 products are gel\nlike and crystalline phases such as silicates and oxy-hydroxides.To predict the\nperformance of the actinide containing waste glass, one needs to understand the\ndissolution process of the glass matrix, the thermodynamic and kinetic\nconstraints which lead to actinide fixation in secondary reaction products as\nwell as the short and long term transport processes.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 28 Apr 2019 13:43:25 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 30 Apr 2019 11:29:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-05-01"}
